28
LA
RESTAURATION
MAXILLO-FACIALE

The
operation
was
carried
out
in
this
way
:

Under
chloroformical
anesthesia
and
after
complete
mus-

cular
resolution,
we
set
in
place
a
mouth
opener;
we
then

enlarged
the
area
of
the
sigmoidal
hollow.
All
along
the
lower

edge
of
the
zygomatical
arcade,
we
execute
a
cutaneous
incision;

after
opening
of
the
two
edges
of
this
incision
we
reach
the
masse-

ter
which
we
incise
vertically
in
the
sense
of
the
fibres,
backward

enough
so
as
not
to
hurt
the
masseteran
nerve;
at
the
bottom

of
this
muscular
gap
and
backwards,
the
digital
exploration

meet
the
neck
of
the
condyle
and
the
insertion
of
the
external

pterygoidian
on
the
antero-internal
pit
excavated
on
this
neck;

when
guiding
by
a
finger
with
the
help
of
a
rugine,
slowly
and

slowly
the
entire
pterygoidian
fibres
are
desinserted.

After
compressing
the
bottom
of
the
wound,
a
small
gauze

drainage
is
made
and
the
teguments
are
sutured.

In
order
to
insure
the
preservation
of
the
correction
of
the

lateral
deviation,
a
guide
prepared
in
advance
was
set
in
place.

The
patient
kept
this
guide
for
two
months
and
continued

to
undergo
massages
of
the
masseter
muscles
and
attend
to

dilatation
sittings.

Once
a
while,
the
guide
was
taken
off
and
then
it
was
found

that
the
deviations
were
not
recurrent.
After
two
months,

the
result
was
considered
as
final
and
the
guide
was
suppressed.

At
present,
the
patient
opens
his
mouth
quite
well,
mas-

ticates
without
a
guide
and
has
fully
recovered.
